### VERDICTS

- **`[V-014-C1]` CONFIRMED** — `session_dedup.fingerprint` is validated for SYNTAX only and never recomputed against current in-scope files — evidence: `mcp_server/lib/validation/spec-doc-structure.ts:636-642` (regex `/^sha256:[a-f0-9]{64}$/` is the sole check), `mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts:1006-1014` (builds the hash at save time but no consumer recomputes it), `spec-doc-structure.ts:1072-1119` (the only content-vs-fingerprint compare requires an explicit `postSavePlan`; not run on completion). — 1-line reasoning: the validator accepts a well-formed sha256 string with no rebind to the file it is supposed to attest.

- **`[V-014-C2]` CONFIRMED** — `CONTINUITY_FRESHNESS` checks only a timestamp lag, not content equality — evidence: `scripts/validation/continuity-freshness.ts:13` (single threshold `10*60*1000 ms`), `continuity-freshness.ts:216-248` (the entire decision is `deltaMs = graphMs - continuityMs; deltaMs > THRESHOLD`); no file read, no content hash, no fingerprint compare happens anywhere in the function. — 1-line reasoning: the rule names "freshness" but only ever compares two ISO timestamps extracted from metadata files.

- **`[V-014-C3]` CONFIRMED** — completion (`validate.sh --strict` + checklist `[x]`) is NOT invalidated by later edits to in-scope files — evidence: `AGENTS.md:247-251` (the COMPLETION VERIFICATION RULE lists only `validate.sh --strict` exit code + checklist `[x]` evidence + metadata reconciliation; no HEAD or content-binding step), `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh` (grep over the full file returns zero matches for `HEAD|fingerprint|git diff|working tree|clean tree` — only the literal string `checklist.md` for level detection, see line 303), `constitutional/verify-before-completion-claims.md:29-30` (the only HEAD-binding clause is gated to **commit/push** claims, not generic completion). — 1-line reasoning: nothing in the spec-kit completion path rebinds a green verdict to current in-scope content or git HEAD.

### NEW_CONSIDERATIONS

- **The fingerprint surface is genuinely close to reusable, not just structural.** `memory-save.ts:1006-1014` already implements `normalizeForFingerprint` + `buildContinuityFingerprint` (newline/trim normalization + sha256); adopting it for completion freshness is a "recompute at validation time" extension, not new infra — strengthens the prior F-002-04 ADAPT recommendation.
- **`validate.sh` has no `--strict` HEAD or tree-state hook at all.** A targeted diff between `validate.sh` (a pure structural/metadata tool) and `verify-before-completion-claims.md:29-30` (the only HEAD-anchored rule, gated to commit/push) is the cleanest place to insert a freshness-binding extension — the surface is empty.
- **Clock-skew path makes C2 even weaker than "lag only".** `continuity-freshness.ts:251-265` treats negative `deltaMs` (continuity newer than graph) as a benign `clock_drift` PASS — so two out-of-order saves can both report `fresh` indefinitely without any content check.

